definition:
The process of identifying outliers. For example, if the mean
for a certain feature is 100 with a standard deviation of 10,
then anomaly detection should flag a value of 200 as suspicious.

A simple and quickly implemented solution to a problem. For example,
&quot;With a heuristic, we achieved 86% accuracy. When we switched to a
deep neural network, accuracy went up to 98%.&quot;
